---
// src/components/Process.astro

const processSteps = [
    {
        step: "01",
        title: "Discovery & Strategic Planning",
        description:
            "Work starts with an in-depth conversation where we understand your business goals, your target audience, and your market environment. We don't just listen, we ask. The result of this phase is a concrete strategic plan and a project roadmap that forms the basis of a successful website.",
    },
    {
        step: "02",
        title: "User Experience (UX) & Design (UI)",
        description:
            "Based on the strategy, we design wireframes and user paths so that the website is logical and easy to use. This is followed by the creation of a modern visual design that fits your brand. The goal is an interface that is not only aesthetic but effectively guides the visitor towards conversion. We only move to the development phase after your approval.",
    },
    {
        step: "03",
        title: "Development & Implementation",
        description:
            "This is where the magic happens. From the approved plans, we write clean, fast, and future-proof code. Thanks to the Astro framework, we build a lightning-fast, SEO-friendly, and perfectly appearing (responsive) website on all devices that meets the most modern technological standards.",
    },

    {
        step: "04",
        title: "Content Upload & Search Engine Optimization",
        description:
            "The ready frame is filled with life: we insert the text and image content. Simultaneously, we perform the basic but critically important search engine optimization (SEO) settings from meta descriptions to image optimization, so that Google immediately loves your new page.",
    },

    {
        step: "05",
        title: "Quality Control & Launch",
        description:
            "Before presenting the website to the world, we test everything meticulously. We check links, forms, browser compatibility, and responsive behavior. Our goal is a flawless, smooth launch that creates a positive impression on visitors from the first minute.",
    },

    {
        step: "06",
        title: "Handover, Training & Support",
        description:
            "After a successful launch, we give you the keys, and if there is a content management system (CMS), we show you how to use it in a short training session. The shared work doesn't end here: if needed, we take care of your website's security, updates, and continuous, smooth operation with our optional maintenance packages.",
    },
];
---

<section class="py-20 md:py-32">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                Steps to a <span
                    class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-sky-400 to-cyan-300"
                    >Successful Project</span
                >
            </h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-300">
                A transparent and efficient process that guarantees the quality
                of the result. No surprises, only predictable progress towards
                the common goal.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="relative max-w-5xl mx-auto">
            <!-- Connecting line for desktop -->
            <div
                class="hidden md:block absolute top-10 left-0 w-full h-0.5 bg-white/10"
            >
            </div>

            <div
                class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-x-12 gap-y-16 relative"
            >
                {
                    processSteps.map((item) => (
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <div class="relative flex items-center justify-center h-20 w-20 rounded-full bg-gray-900 border-2 border-white/10 text-sky-400 text-3xl font-bold mx-auto mb-6 z-10">
                                {item.step}
                            </div>
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">
                                {item.title}
                            </h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-300">{item.description}</p>
                        </div>
                    ))
                }
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
